heading_16 = heading_15 + ">>36. Application of Chapter V; The provisions of this Chapter apply to all persons charged with any offence against the statute law of Western Australia.; The provisions of this Chapter apply to all persons charged with any offence against the statute law of Western Australia.; The provisions of this Chapter apply to all persons charged with any offence against the statute law of Western Australia."
heading_17 = heading_16 + ">>heading1"
CONTEXT(heading_17, 'Chapter 6  Criminal liability of officers of bodies corporate  [Heading inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_17 = heading_15 + ">>37. Overview"
heading_18 = heading_17 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_18, 'This Chapter contains a set of standard provisions (sections 39, 40 and 41) that set out certain circumstances in which directors and other officers of a body corporate can incur criminal liability as a result of an offence by the body corporate.')
heading_19 = heading_17 + ">>(2) Only one of sections 39, 40 and 41 can apply to an offence."
CONTEXT(heading_19, '[Section 37 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_18 = heading_15 + ">>38. Term used officer; In this Chapter ; In this Chapter ; In this Chapter "
heading_19 = heading_18 + ">>officer, in relation to a body corporate, has the meaning given in the  Corporations Act 2001  (Commonwealth) section 9."
CONTEXT(heading_19, '[Section 38 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_19 = heading_15 + ">>39. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on prosecution to prove reasonable steps not taken"
heading_20 = heading_19 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_20, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_21 = heading_19 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence if the officer failed to take all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_22 = heading_19 + ">>(3) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_25, '[Section 39 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_20 = heading_15 + ">>40. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on prosecution to prove reasonable steps not taken if evidence suggesting reasonable steps adduced"
heading_21 = heading_20 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_21, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_22 = heading_20 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence unless the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_23 = heading_20 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'The prosecutor has the onus of proving that the officer failed to take all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate if, and only if, evidence that suggests a reasonable possibility that the officer took all reasonable steps is first adduced by or on behalf of the officer.')
heading_24 = heading_20 + ">>(4) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_27 = heading_24 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_27, '[Section 40 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_21 = heading_15 + ">>41. Officer liability for corporate offence onus on officer to prove reasonable steps taken"
heading_22 = heading_21 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_22, 'This section applies to an offence if a provision of this Code, or of another written law, expressly provides that it applies to the offence.')
heading_23 = heading_21 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'If a body corporate is guilty of an offence to which this section applies, an officer of the body corporate is also guilty of the offence unless the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_24 = heading_21 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'The officer has the onus of proving that the officer took all reasonable steps to prevent the commission of the offence by the body corporate.')
heading_25 = heading_21 + ">>(4) In determining whether things done or omitted to be done by the officer constitute reasonable steps, a court must have regard to "
heading_26 = heading_25 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'what the officer knew, or ought to have known, about the commission of the offence by the body corporate and')
heading_27 = heading_25 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'whether the officer was in a position to influence the conduct of the body corporate in relation to the commission of the offence and')
heading_28 = heading_25 + ">>(c) any other relevant matter."
CONTEXT(heading_28, '[Section 41 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_22 = heading_15 + ">>42. Further provisions relating to criminal liability of officers of bodies corporate"
heading_23 = heading_22 + ">>(1)"
CONTEXT(heading_23, 'This Chapter does not affect the liability of a body corporate for any offence.')
heading_24 = heading_22 + ">>(2)"
CONTEXT(heading_24, 'This Chapter does not affect the liability of an officer, or any other person, under Chapters II, LVII, LVIII and LIX.')
heading_25 = heading_22 + ">>(3)"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'An officer of a body corporate may be charged with, and convicted of, an offence in accordance with section 39, 40 or 41 whether or not the body corporate is charged with, or convicted of, the offence committed by the body corporate.')
heading_26 = heading_22 + ">>(4) If an officer of a body corporate who is charged with an offence in accordance with section 39, 40 or 41 claims that the body"
heading_27 = heading_26 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_27, 'the onus of proving the defence is on the officer and')
heading_28 = heading_26 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_28, 'the standard of proof required is the standard that would apply to the body corporate in relation to the defence.')
heading_27 = heading_22 + ">>(5) Subsection (4) does not limit any other defence available to the officer."
CONTEXT(heading_27, '[Section 42 inserted No. 9 of 2023 s. 5.]')
heading_23 = heading_15 + ">>43. Penalties"
heading_24 = heading_23 + ">>(1) This section applies to an offence if "
heading_25 = heading_24 + ">>a"
CONTEXT(heading_25, 'section 39, 40 or 41 applies to the offence and')
heading_26 = heading_24 + ">>b"
CONTEXT(heading_26, 'the specified penalty for the offence applies only to a body corporate.')
